race.comment: MYSTIC WONDER (1) is a progressive mare that bolted in first-up. Suspect there was plenty of improvement there so she looks hard to beat again. Drawn perfectly and maps to get the ideal run near the speed. She might be better than these and can win again. SWIFTIE HARRIET (5) has more ability than her record suggests this preparation. She was plain behind MYSTIC WONDER last start but her prior form puts her right in the frame here. ANGEL TORQUE (3) won an easier race last start but looks progressive and will be better suited up to the 1250m. She will park behind the speed and if she gets some luck, she can finish in the money. Others to consider for exotics are PALM OF JUMEIRAH (6) and KERSEE (7).
